# Changelog and Development Plan Management

## üìã Overview

This project maintains two key documents for tracking changes and planning:

1. **CHANGELOG.md**: Detailed history of all changes with dates
2. **DEVELOPMENT_PLAN.md**: Roadmap, planned features, and timeline

## Changelog Format

### Structure

Follow [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/) format:

```markdown
## [Version] - YYYY-MM-DD

### Added
- New features

### Changed
- Changes to existing features

### Fixed
- Bug fixes

### Documentation
- Documentation updates
```

### Date Format

- Use ISO 8601 format: `YYYY-MM-DD`
- Example: `2025-01-15`

### Version Format

- Follow [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/)
- Format: `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`
- Example: `0.1.0`, `0.2.0`, `1.0.0`

## Development Plan Format

### Structure

```markdown
## Phase X: Name (Status: Planned/In Progress/Completed)

### Features
- [ ] Feature name (Priority: High/Medium/Low)
  - Description
  - Estimated: X days
```

### Status Indicators

- `‚úÖ Complete` - Feature is done
- `üîÑ In Progress` - Currently being developed
- `üìã Planned` - Planned for future
- `‚ùå Cancelled` - No longer planned

### Priority Levels

- **High**: Next sprint, critical features
- **Medium**: Next quarter, important features
- **Low**: Future, nice-to-have features

## Update Workflow

### When Adding a Feature

1. **Update DEVELOPMENT_PLAN.md**
   ```markdown
   - [ ] Feature name (Priority: Medium)
     - Description
     - Estimated: 2 days
   ```

2. **Develop the feature**
   - Follow Cursor Rules
   - Write tests
   - Update documentation
   - Commit with descriptive message

3. **Get commit hash**
   ```bash
   git log --oneline -1
   # Output: abc1234 Add feature name
   ```

4. **Update CHANGELOG.md**
   ```markdown
   ## [0.2.0] - 2025-02-01
   
   ### Added
   - **Feature name** ([abc1234](https://github.com/user/repo/commit/abc1234))
     - Description of what was added
   ```

5. **Update DEVELOPMENT_PLAN.md**
   ```markdown
   - [x] Feature name (Priority: Medium) ‚úÖ
   ```

### When Fixing a Bug

1. **Fix the bug**
   - Commit with descriptive message
   - Get commit hash: `git log --oneline -1`

2. **Update CHANGELOG.md**
   ```markdown
   ### Fixed
   - **Bug description** ([abc1234](https://github.com/user/repo/commit/abc1234))
     - What was fixed
   ```

### When Changing Existing Features

1. **Make the change**
2. **Update CHANGELOG.md**
   ```markdown
   ### Changed
   - Feature name
     - What changed and why
   ```

## Best Practices

### DO:
- ‚úÖ Update CHANGELOG.md for every release
- ‚úÖ Use clear, descriptive change descriptions
- ‚úÖ Group changes by type (Added, Changed, Fixed)
- ‚úÖ Include dates for all changes
- ‚úÖ Update DEVELOPMENT_PLAN.md when planning features
- ‚úÖ Mark completed features in DEVELOPMENT_PLAN.md
- ‚úÖ Estimate effort for planned features
- ‚úÖ Update timeline when priorities change

### DON'T:
- ‚ùå Don't forget to update CHANGELOG.md
- ‚ùå Don't use vague descriptions
- ‚ùå Don't skip dates
- ‚ùå Don't leave DEVELOPMENT_PLAN.md outdated
- ‚ùå Don't forget to mark completed features
- ‚ùå Don't mix different change types in one entry

